         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>144</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... water (may not be) drunk by the miserable <hi>Preta</hi>s ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he should do ... Who ... the four great elements ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he might (not?) obtain the lack ... not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... fear of dying of thirst ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... perished. || Then they ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... dry [or] humid bodies ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>233</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... like (?) ... having come towards the Buddha, the teacher, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they were standing with tearful eyes ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... we, venerable, seven ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... out of [their?] will ... big like mountains ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>308</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for some ... 70 years ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>352</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... when we will come close to ..., then ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">The leaf number may be 47 or 48, since it seems to belong together with the story in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a39"/> - <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a42"/>.</note><note corresp="#a6" type="philcomment"><hi>āsunt lewaṃ</hi>: cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegetal1931"/><citedRange>37, 252</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment"><hi>c kātse</hi>: <hi>c</hi> is probably an allative.</note></p>
